def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)

    if isinstance(key, list):
        groupings = []
        exclusions = []
        for k in key:
            grouping = Grouping(
                group_axis,
                k,
                obj=obj,
                name=k,
                level=level,
                sort=sort,
                observed=observed,
                in_axis=True
            )
            groupings.append(grouping)
            exclusions.append(k)
    else:
        grouping = Grouping(
            group_axis,
            key,
            obj=obj,
            name=key,
            level=level,
            sort=sort,
            observed=observed,
            in_axis=True
        )
        groupings = [grouping]
        exclusions = [key]

    grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
    return grouper, exclusions, obj
